        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 15 at 9:12PM MDT by NWS Albuquerque NM</headline>
        <description>At 912 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking an area of strong
thunderstorms extending from 7 miles north of Variadero to 15 miles
east of Conchas, and is nearly stationary.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Conchas Dam, Conchas, Conchas Lake State Park, Variadero, Bell
Ranch and Trementina.

This includes State Road 104 between Mile Markers 44 and 53...and
between Mile Markers 59 and 98.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
